{[#]} 9... c6 10. Bf2 d5 11. exd5 cxd5 12. O-O Nc6 13. c5 Nh5 14. Qd2 Be5 {
Provoking weaknesses on the light squares.} 15. g3 {[%csl Rf3,Rg1,Rh3]} Ng7 16.
Rfd1 Bf5 $1 {A pawn sacrifice to centralize the pieces} 17. Rac1 (17. Nxf5 Nxf5
{[%cal Gf5d4]} 18. Nxd5 (18. Qxd5 Qxd5 19. Nxd5 Bxb2 $17) 18... Nfd4 19. Nc3
Qe7 20. Kg2 Rad8 $36) 17... Bxd4 $1 {Another counter-intuitive move with the
goal to centralize the knight.} 18. Bxd4 Ne6 19. Bf2 d4 20. Nb5 Qd5 {and} 21.
b4 $6 {[#] White's play is too static.} ({More critical moves were} 21. g4 Bxg4
22. fxg4 Ng5 23. Rc3 Qe5) (21. Nd6) 21... Ng5 $1 {Exploiting weaknesses on the
light squares by tactical means.} (21... Rad8 22. Nd6 Bh3 23. Nxe8 Rxe8 $44) (
21... a5 $5 22. bxa5 Rxa5) (21... d3 $5 22. Bxd3 Ne5 23. Be2 Nxf3+ 24. Bxf3
Qxf3 25. Qe3 Qh5 26. Nd6 Ng5 $13) 22. Nc7 Rxe2 $1 {Eliminating the main
defender of the light squares.} (22... Qxf3 23. Bxf3 Nxf3+ 24. Kg2 Nxd2 25.
Rxd2) (22... Nxf3+ 23. Bxf3 Qxf3 24. Qf4) 23. Qxe2 Nxf3+ 24. Kh1 d3 $1 {
The key idea.} 25. Qe3 Qd7 26. Nxa8 $2 {[#] Completely ignoring the kingside.}
(26. Qxf3 Qxc7 27. g4 $1 Ne5 28. Bg3 $13) 26... Ng5 $1 {White king is
defenceless on the light squares now.} (26... Nfe5 27. Nc7 Qxc7 28. Be1 $1 Qd7
29. Bc3 Qd5+ 30. Kg1 $13) 27. Kg1 (27. Qxg5 Be4+ 28. Kg1 Qh3 $19) 27... Ne5 28.
c6 bxc6 29. Rc5 Nef3+ 30. Kh1 Be4 31. Rxd3 Qh3 32. Rd8+ Kg7 33. Bg1 Nxh2+ 34.
Qxe4 Nhf3+ {A beautiful attacking game by a relatively unknown young player
from Iran.} 0-1

