{[#] Black can often hold on to the draw thanks to his active bishop even when
down a pawn:} 32... Bc4 33. Rd2 Rd8 34. Nb4 Rxd2 35. Kxd2 c5 36. Nc6 Bxa2 37.
Nxa7 f4 38. Nc6 Kg7 39. Ne5 Bd5 40. Nd3 Bxg2 41. Nxf4 Ba8 42. Ne6+ Kf6 43. Nxc5
Kg5 44. Ke3 Kg4 45. Kf2 Kh3 46. Kg1 Kg4 47. Nd7 Kf3 48. c4 Ke4 49. Kf2 Kd4 50.
Kg3 Bc6 51. Nf6 Kxc4 52. Kf4 Ba4 53. Nxh7 Kd5 54. Ng5 Kd6 55. Ne4+ Ke7 {
1/2-1/2 The game is a draw.} 1/2-1/2

