{[#] In this position Black is clearly better thanks to the active position of
his bishop, the limited white knight on g3 and above all-due to the
overextended position of his pawns.} 29... Nd7 {Brings the knight to the
optimal square.} 30. Ne6 Rf6 {[%csl Gc7]} 31. Raf1 ({The immediate capture
does not yield White anything after:} 31. Nxc7 Rc8 32. Ne6 Rxc4 $17) 31... Ne5
32. Kc3 ({But this was a good moment to capture:} 32. Nxc7 Rc8 33. Ne6 Rxc4 34.
Nh5 Rg6 35. Nhf4 {as the poor knight gets back into the game.}) 32... Rg8 33.
Ng5 (33. Ne4 $2 Rxg1) 33... h6 34. N3e4 ({The pin loses White's position in
case of:} 34. Nxf3 Rxf3+ 35. Rxf3 Nxf3 36. Rg2 Nxh4 37. Rg1 Nf3 38. Rg2 h5 $19)
(34. N5e4 Rf4) 34... Rf4 {The overextended white pawns start to tell.} 35. Nxf3
Rxg1 36. Rxg1 Rxf3+ 37. Kb4 (37. Kd4 Rd3#) 37... Rf4 38. Nd2 Rxh4 {Winning the
important pawn and the game.} 39. b3 Rd4 40. Rg2 axb3 41. axb3 h5 42. Kc3 Rf4
43. c5 h4 44. cxd6 cxd6 45. Nc4 h3 46. Rh2 Rf3+ 47. Kb4 Ng4 48. Rh1 Nf2 (48...
Rg3 49. Nxd6 Nf2 50. Nf7+ (50. Rh2 Rg2 51. Nf7+ Kg7 52. d6 Kxf7) 50... Kg7 51.
d6) 49. Rh2 Ne4 50. Na5 Kg7 51. Nxb7 Kf6 52. Re2 Rf4 (52... Ke5 53. Nxd6) 53.
Ka5 Nf2 54. Nxd6 Kg6 (54... h2 55. Rxf2 h1=Q (55... Rxf2 56. Ne4+ Ke5 57. Nxf2
$18) 56. Rxf4+ Ke5 57. Rc4 Kxd6 58. Kb4) 55. Nc4 h2 56. Re1 Rf5 {0-1 White
resigns.} 0-1

[Event "Manila (izt)"]
