{In the last example related to this pawn structure, we shall take a look at a
typical tactical idea that you should always have in mind. This idea works
very well when the opponent is in a passive position. In this position, Vaulin
played the thematic} 19. Ndb5 $1 {White sacrifices a piece for two pawns and
strong centre. Additionally, Black's pieces are poorly coordinated. In this
specific position, White can even immediately regain the material.} cxb5 20.
Nxb5 Qe7 21. Nxd6 {[%csl Rc5,Re8]} Na6 22. Nxe8 Qxe8 23. Bd4 Bxd4+ 24. Rxd4 $18
{Besides his better coordination, White has already the material advantage.
Black's position is hopeless.} Bd7 25. Qd2 Nc5 26. Rd1 Qe7 27. e5 h5 28. Rd6 h4
29. g4 g5 30. f5 Bc6 31. Bxc6 bxc6 32. Qe3 Ncd7 33. e6 fxe6 34. fxe6 Nb8 35.
Rd8 Kg7 36. Qe5+ 1-0

