and White is not in time to cover both of his hanging pawns.}) 13... a6 ({
As always, the move} 13... Ne6 {is well met by} 14. Nde2 {when Black faces
huge spatial problems.} a6 {was seen in Vachier Lagrave, M - Topalov, V
Istanbul 2012 Now, I think that White should restrict any possible counterplay
by means of} 15. a4 $5 $146 a5 16. Be3 b6 17. Qc2 Nc5 18. b3 $14 {yielding c5
for the knight did not solve Black's strategic problems, and now White can
