{Let's take a look at another game in which the same position has been reached.
This time, instead of 13...Ne8, Black went for} 13... Nxe5 {This move, however,
gives White a free hand in the centre.} 14. Nxe5 Qxe5 15. Bf4 $1 {The most
precise continuation. White is planning to follow with e4-e5.} Qh5 16. e5 Nd5
$2 {After this move, White obtains a huge advantage.} ({More to the point
would have been} 16... Bf5 $1 17. Qd2 Nd7 18. g4 Bxg4 19. hxg4 Qxg4 20. Qxd7
Qxf4 21. Qxc6 Bxe5 {when Black retains some compensation for the piece.}) 17.
Nxd5 cxd5 18. Rxd5 Bf5 19. Qd2 Bxh3 20. e6 Qg4 21. e7 Rfe8 22. Rd8 Bxg2 23.
Kxg2 Bd4 24. Rxa8 Rxa8 25. Re1 Re8 26. b4 f6 27. bxc5 Qd7 28. Kg1 g5 29. Bd6
Qg4 30. Kg2 Be5 1-0

