[EventCountry "NED"]

{David Bronstein decides to enter our pawn structure, but Petrosian reacts
very strong and easily levels the game.} 14. exf5 gxf5 15. f4 e4 16. Be3 {
If White plays something else, then 16...Bd4 could be very annoying.} h6 17.
Nh3 (17. Ne6 $5 {deserves attention} Nxe6 18. dxe6 Nb6 19. Qb3 Bxe6 20. Rad1 {
White has some compensation, but probably not enough for equality.}) 17... Bxc3
$1 {An amazing move which completely levels the game. Both White's bishops are
passive and blocked by his own pawns. Also, White has no longer ideas to
penetrate the queenside by playing b2-b4. Petrosian said in his comments that
this move is hard to make only psychologically.} (17... b5 $5 {Playing in a
Benko style also gives Black good play.} 18. cxb5 a6 {Black has the initiative.
}) 18. bxc3 Nf6 19. a4 Kh8 20. Nf2 {the only constructive idea for White is
g2-g4, but Black easily can stop this.} Rg8 21. Kh1 Qe8 22. Rg1 Qg6 23. Qd2 Bd7
24. g3 Rae8 25. a5 Re7 26. Rab1 Bc8 27. Rg2 Reg7 28. Rbg1 Nce8 29. h3 h5 {
Draw in a slightly better position for Black. He has an idea to make a passed
pawn on the queenside later.} 1/2-1/2

