{Black has just played f7-f5, challenging the centre. How to react?} 13. exf5
$1 {Black can't capture with a knight, so transposing to the Botvinnik
structure is a right choice here.} gxf5 14. f4 $1 {Fixing the f4 pawn.} e4 15.
Bd2 {White starts regrouping his pieces.} Ndf6 16. Ne3 {The knight is coming
to the perfect e3-square.} Nc7 17. c4 {Protecting completely the d5-pawn} Na8
18. Bc3 {Finally the bishop is coming to the long diagonal. White is ready to
open the queenside by b2-b4 in an appropriate moment.} 1-0

