{[#]} 12. g5 {This is a new concept. White is trying to restrict Black's
pieces on the kingside.} Ne8 13. h4 f5 14. h5 f4 $4 {The position was already
hard, but this move is a positional suicide} 15. Bxc5 dxc5 16. h6 {Game over.
The trimph of White's strategy. Black's bishop can't join the game anymore and
now White is playing like he has an extra piece. Just exchange everything.} Bh8
17. Bg4 Nd6 18. Bxd7 Qxd7 19. Qf3 Rab8 20. a4 Rf7 21. b3 Qd8 22. Rg1 Qb6 23.
Kd1 Qd8 24. Kc2 b6 25. dxc6 Rc7 26. Qg4 Nf7 27. Rad1 Rxc6 28. Nf3 Qe8 {[%csl
Rd1]} 29. Qd7 (29. Rd7 {[%cal Rg1d1] Finished the game quicker}) 29... Kf8 30.
Qxe8+ $18 {and I won in 20 moves} 1-0

