{[#]} 13. b3 {In this example, I want to illustrate to you another idea for
Black. Sometimes, Black is not going for an f7-f5 break, but b7-b5.} g5 $1 {
After this move, f7-f5, is no longer good, but Black strikes on the other
flang.} 14. Bg3 cxd5 15. cxd5 b5 16. b4 (16. f3 {is the engine suggestion, but
it seems scary to allow b5-b4} b4 17. Na4 Nxa4 18. bxa4 Nh5 $13) 16... axb4 17.
Rxb4 Qa5 18. Qb1 Na6 19. Rb3 Nc5 20. Rb4 Na6 21. Rb3 Rfc8 22. Qb2 b4 {Black
gets the iniative and went to win a nice game} 0-1

