{We can reach the "Mar Del Plata" Structure from other openings as well} 1. e4
e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. c3 a6 6. Ba4 d6 7. d4 Bd7 8. d5 (8. Re1 {
Recently, White discovered that it is better to delay d4-d5 push}) 8... Nce7 9.
Bxd7+ Qxd7 10. c4 h6 {It is important to stop Ng5, before playing f7-f5.} 11.
Nc3 f5 {Compare to KID, Black wins several tempis, because he played first f5
and then Nf6, but as a compensation White already exchanged the light-squared
bishops.} 12. Nd2 Nf6 13. f3 O-O 14. b4 c6 $1 {Another important strategical
idea. Without the light-squared bishops, "f5-f4" is not good for Black. Taking
on e4 is also not a good idea. On the other hand, White is ready for c4-c5.
Carlsen's move is a prophylactic against "c4-c5"} 15. dxc6 Nxc6 16. a3 Nd4 $15
{Black is already slightly better, but the game eventually ended in a draw.}
1/2-1/2

