1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Be2 e5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d5
Ne7 9. Nd2 {The move 9.Nd2 is a very dangerous system that, in the last years,
is in the shadow of 9.b4 and 9.Ne1. White's idea is to push "c4-c5" followed
by Nc4} c6 {Black has many possible ways to react here, the main one is 9...a5,
but I find the move in the game very instructive.} 10. Rb1 ({The typical} 10.
b4 {failed to pose any problems after:} a5 11. bxa5 c5 $11 {Black closes the
centre and there is no "b2-b4" break for White}) 10... b5 {The point of
Black's previous move} 11. dxc6 b4 12. Nd5 Nxc6 13. Nxf6+ Qxf6 14. b3 Bb7 {
Black has nothing to worry about and comfortably drew the game} 1/2-1/2

